# MIYAR UI Redesign — Premium Interior Design Experience

## Goal

Transform MIYAR from a functional dark-themed dashboard into a **premium interior design intelligence platform** that feels like a luxury hotel lobby meets a Bloomberg terminal. Update the pre-login homepage to showcase real app capabilities and add a version changelog. Streamline the dashboard sidebar for easier navigation.

## Design References (Stitch Mockups)

- **Homepage**: [Stitch Project](https://stitch.withgoogle.com/project/11215202624286097747) — Screen `b1df75f72e6d4469a38322fef422e245`
- **Dashboard**: Screen `58a301ee7c03459893fe337d8f83c280`

## Design System

| Token | Current | New |
|-------|---------|-----|
| **Primary** | Generic blue | Warm Gold `#C9A96E` |
| **Background** | `--background` dark | Deep Navy `#0A1628` |
| **Card BG** | `--card` | Charcoal `#111827` with glass blur |
| **Accent** | Generic | Champagne `#E8D5B7` |
| **Font** | System default | **Manrope** (Google Fonts) |
| **Border radius** | Mixed | `12px` (cards), `8px` (buttons) |
| **Glassmorphism** | None | `backdrop-filter: blur(16px)` + `bg-opacity-60` |

